    <note>Shi Kan [1467] According to Ge Shengzhong [7263], Kan's [1467] uncle, Daren [3723], passed the jinshi in 1073 when more than forty jinshi came from Changzhou, among them the head of the list Yu Zhong [4133]. Daren's father was the first of his immediate ancestors to hold office. The family originally lived in Jiangning, but moved to Changzhou, Wujin xian during the Southern Tang. Gai's [1468] cousin. Zhang Kuo, WJ, 13.22a; Ge Shengzhong, WJ, 12.18b-19b, 22b, 23a.</note>
